{
  "plan": {
    "id": "subagent-delegation-ux",
    "revision": 2,
    "context": {
      "cartographer_findings": [
        "UX-001: Slash-popover lacks group headers for subagent categories (MEDIUM)",
        "UX-002: Subagent ordering — currently sorted by mode === 'primary' first, then alphabetical by name (LOW)",
        "UX-003: @mention autocomplete needs subagent type support (MEDIUM) — ALREADY IMPLEMENTED via delegate type",
        "UX-004: No frecency/usage ranking for recently used subagents (LOW) — DEFERRED",
        "UX-005: Keyboard navigation — arrow keys lose cursor position (MEDIUM) — ALREADY HANDLED via event.preventDefault() in handleKeyDown",
        "UX-006: Subagent data not cached between dialog opens (LOW) — ALREADY CACHED via sync.data.agent reactive store",
        "UX-007: No visual indicator for currently selected subagent (LOW) — ALREADY VISIBLE as agent pill in editor"
      ],
      "cross_session_insight": "Two different agent filter pipelines exist: @mention excludes mode==='primary', composer dropdown excludes mode==='subagent'. Unify filter logic."
    },
    "root_causes": [
      {
        "hypothesis": "The @-mention popover's useFilteredList hook already computes grouped data via its groupBy/sortGroupsBy options, but the grouped resource is silently ignored. Only the flat array is passed to PromptPopover, which renders items in one unbroken list.",
        "confidence": "high",
        "evidence": [
          "useFilteredList returns { grouped: Resource<Group[]>, flat: Memo<T[]> }",
          "prompt-input.tsx destructures only flat/active/setActive/onInput/onKeyDown from the at-mention useFilteredList call, ignoring grouped",
          "PromptPopover receives atFlat: AtOption[] and renders with <For each={props.atFlat.slice(0, 10)}> — no section headers"
        ]
      },
      {
        "hypothesis": "Three independent filter expressions exist (local.tsx, prompt-input.tsx, dialog-manage-agents.tsx) with different exclusion criteria (mode !== 'subagent' vs mode !== 'primary'), creating a maintainability seam.",
        "confidence": "high",
        "evidence": [
          "context/local.tsx:64: sync.data.agent.filter((item) => item.mode !== 'subagent' && !item.hidden)",
          "prompt-input.tsx:585: sync.data.agent.filter((agent) => !agent.hidden && agent.mode !== 'primary')",
          "dialog-manage-agents.tsx:53: (sync.data.agent ?? []).filter((a) => a.mode !== 'subagent' && !a.hidden)"
        ]
      },
      {
        "hypothesis": "Items within @-mention groups appear in server-defined order because useFilteredList is not configured with sortBy, unlike the DialogManageAgents list which uses sortBy: (a, b) => a.name.localeCompare(b.name).",
        "confidence": "medium",
        "evidence": [
          "useFilteredList supports sortBy: (a: T, b: T) => number but it's not passed in the at-mention call",
          "DialogManageAgents uses sortBy at line ~70 for alphabetical ordering"
        ]
      }
    ],
    "fixes": [
      {
        "id": "fix-A",
        "description": "Group headers for @-mention popover — plumb useFilteredList's grouped resource to PromptPopover and render localized section headers",
        "files": [
          "packages/app/src/components/prompt-input/slash-popover.tsx",
          "packages/app/src/components/prompt-input.tsx"
        ],
        "before": "PromptPopover receives atFlat: AtOption[] and renders: <For each={props.atFlat.slice(0, 10)}> with no visual group separation. Agent, delegate, recent file, and file items interleaved in one list.",
        "after": "PromptPopover receives atGrouped: { category: string; items: AtOption[] }[]. Renders each group with a section header (e.g. 'Agents', 'Subagents', 'Recent Files', 'Files') using the t() translation function. Items capped at 10 total across all groups (preserving existing limit). Falls back to flat render if atGrouped is empty.",
        "impact": {
          "affected_files": [
            "packages/app/src/components/prompt-input/slash-popover.tsx",
            "packages/app/src/components/prompt-input.tsx"
          ],
          "tests_to_run": [
            "cd packages/app && bun test --filter 'prompt-input'",
            "cd packages/app && bun typecheck"
          ]
        },
        "risks": [
          "Group[] type must match useFilteredList's Group shape: { category: string; items: T[] } — cast or type-align",
          "The 10-item slice limit shifts from a flat global cap to a total-across-groups cap — slightly different distribution but same total count",
          "Header labels need translation keys — at minimum 'Subagents' since 'Agents' may already exist",
          "If useFilteredList grouped Resource is still loading (initialValue: []), atGrouped will be empty array — graceful fallback to flat render needed"
        ],
        "validation": [
          "Open @-mention popover with multiple agents/subagents/files — verify section headers appear with correct labels",
          "Verify at most 10 items total appear when >10 items exist across all groups",
          "Verify ArrowUp/Down cycle correctly through items across group boundaries",
          "Verify clicking a group header area does not trigger item selection",
          "Check localization works — switch language and verify header labels update"
        ]
      },
      {
        "id": "fix-B",
        "description": "Alphabetical ordering within @-mention groups — add sortBy to useFilteredList call",
        "files": [
          "packages/app/src/components/prompt-input.tsx"
        ],
        "before": "Items inside each group appear in the order returned by agentList() and file search (server-defined order for agents, arbitrary for files).",
        "after": "sortBy: (a, b) => { if (a.type === 'agent' || a.type === 'delegate') return a.name.localeCompare(b.name); if (a.type === 'file' && b.type === 'file') return a.path.localeCompare(b.path); return 0 } applied to the at-mention useFilteredList call. Agents sorted alphabetically, subagents sorted alphabetically, files sorted by path.",
        "impact": {
          "affected_files": [
            "packages/app/src/components/prompt-input.tsx"
          ],
          "tests_to_run": [
            "cd packages/app && bun test --filter 'prompt-input'",
            "cd packages/app && bun typecheck"
          ]
        },
        "risks": [
          "Trivial change — sortBy operates only on items after groupBy, within each group. Cannot affect which items appear.",
          "localeCompare is stable across modern JS engines",
          "Must handle the case where (a.type, b.type) are different type union branches (e.g. agent vs file) — the current guard clauses handle this via type narrowing"
        ],
        "validation": [
          "Open @-mention popover with multiple agents — verify alphabetical order",
          "Open with multiple subagents — verify alphabetical order",
          "Open with files — verify path order",
          "Verify mixed agent+file popover — agents still in their own group, files in theirs"
        ]
      },
      {
        "id": "fix-C",
        "description": "Shared agent filter utility — extract duplicated inline filter logic into named functions",
        "files": [
          "packages/app/src/utils/agent-filter.ts",
          "packages/app/src/context/local.tsx",
          "packages/app/src/components/prompt-input.tsx",
          "packages/app/src/components/dialog-manage-agents.tsx"
        ],
        "before": "Three inline filter expressions:\n  // local.tsx: sync.data.agent.filter((item) => item.mode !== 'subagent' && !item.hidden)\n  // prompt-input.tsx: sync.data.agent.filter((agent) => !agent.hidden && agent.mode !== 'primary')\n  // dialog-manage-agents.tsx: (sync.data.agent ?? []).filter((a) => a.mode !== 'subagent' && !a.hidden)",
        "after": "New file packages/app/src/utils/agent-filter.ts exports:\n  agentsForDropdown(agents) — filters mode !== 'subagent', !hidden\n  agentsForMention(agents) — filters !hidden, mode !== 'primary'\nConsumers use:\n  // local.tsx: agentsForDropdown(sync.data.agent)\n  // prompt-input.tsx: agentsForMention(sync.data.agent)\n  // dialog-manage-agents.tsx: agentsForDropdown(sync.data.agent ?? [])",
        "impact": {
          "affected_files": [
            "packages/app/src/utils/agent-filter.ts",
            "packages/app/src/context/local.tsx",
            "packages/app/src/components/prompt-input.tsx",
            "packages/app/src/components/dialog-manage-agents.tsx"
          ],
          "tests_to_run": [
            "cd packages/app && bun typecheck",
            "cd packages/app && bun test"
          ]
        },
        "risks": [
          "dialog-manage-agents.tsx is dirty (uncommitted changes from session ses_189c0383effe). Must use search_replace with expected_before_sha256 or add change additively.",
          "Agent type must be imported from @opencode-ai/sdk/v2/gen/types.gen — verify the path resolves in the app's tsconfig.",
          "The nullish fallback (sync.data.agent ?? []) in dialog-manage-agents must be preserved since it handles the loading state where sync.data.agent could be null/undefined.",
          "Behavior must match exactly: same field access, same filter logic."
        ],
        "validation": [
          "Verify agent dropdown (ComposerAgentControl) still shows same agents as before",
          "Verify @-mention popover still shows subagents + all-mode agents",
          "Verify manage agents dialog still shows same set",
          "Run typecheck to confirm Agent type import resolves",
          "Run test suite to confirm no regressions"
        ]
      }
    ],
    "apply_order": ["fix-B", "fix-A", "fix-C"],
    "rationale": "fix-B (sortBy) is the smallest change and has zero UI impact on its own — apply first to validate the edit workflow. fix-A (group headers) is the primary visible change but depends only on existing hook infrastructure. fix-C (shared filter utility) touches a dirty file (dialog-manage-agents.tsx) and requires careful edit preservation — apply last after the mechanical changes are validated.",
    "rollback_plan": "Revert in reverse apply order: (1) restore inline filter expressions in local.tsx, prompt-input.tsx, dialog-manage-agents.tsx — delete agent-filter.ts. (2) Revert atGrouped prop and group header rendering in slash-popover.tsx/prompt-input.tsx — restore flat rendering. (3) Remove sortBy from useFilteredList call."
  }
}
